Posted: January 17, 2016
Early Access Review
								#include <stddisclaimer.h> // This is an early access review. Deal with it.First up, this is a game I have no trouble recommending you pay for in Early Access form. Why? Because it's remarkably free of bugs, glitches, and in a fully playable - albeit incomplete - state. This game is what Valve should REQUIRE developers to have before they're allowed to sell Early Access. So yes. What you'll be getting is a completely playable game, minus some mechanics. Is it going to crash on you? Honestly, probably not! Is it release ready? Well hell, Prison Architect released missing a lot more than this seems to be. There really is no reason to NOT buy this game before release! Even if the developers up and vanish into the aether tomorrow? You're going to keep playing this game. If you got into GDT (and who didn't?), either you're going to love Mad Games Tycoon or you're going to hate it. Think of it as a more complex GDT in some areas, less in others, with a dash of Hospital Tycoon thrown in and Airline Tycoon too. (I think it was Airline Tycoon I'm thinking of.) Hire developers! Wait, hold up. Build an office, buy furniture, THEN hire developers! Release ga-oh, crap, it's full of bugs. Build a QA department! Wait, I need to resear-build a Research Office! Get the idea? Don't feel like the hassle of developing games? Then build and license engines instead and release a game once every 8 years or so! (OHAI EPIC!) Sick of the competition? Amass a fortune, buy them out, and SHUT THEM ALL DOWN. Build a console and destroy those losers at Poni! There's no wrong way to play, and the added complexity creates DEPTH instead of "do X for X's sake" grinding.10/10 would buy Idi Software and consign to a life of grinding FPSes for me to publish again
